## SIFT evidence chain — auditd rules (Phase 17b)
##
## Watches all write and attribute-change operations in the cases root and the
## SIFT state directory. Attribute changes (perm=a) include chmod and chattr
## calls — so deliberate clearing of the +i immutable flag is recorded in the
## kernel audit log with UID, PID, binary path, and timestamp.
##
## Query writes:   ausearch -k sift_evidence_write --format text
## Query core:     ausearch -k sift_core_write --format text
##
## CASES_ROOT is substituted by install.sh at deploy time.
## Default: /cases

-a always,exit -F dir=CASES_ROOT -F perm=wa -F key=sift_evidence_write
-a always,exit -F dir=/var/lib/sift -F perm=wa -F key=sift_core_write
